:: Arrival [cluster1 passage]
You arrive at the Bruised Banana.

A quiet house in Portland where something unusual is underway. Laptops open on tables. Whiteboards filled with fragments of strategy. Someone left a mug of tea beside a stack of notes.

You've stepped into the early days of a three-month build experiment.

[[Continue|The Work]]

:: The Work [cluster1 passage]
The work happening here began as a book called ''Mastering the Game of Allyship''.

Over time the idea outgrew the page.

The framework started behaving like a game — something people could step into together. Conversations became quests. Emotional shifts turned into visible moves. Coordination became part of the story.

[[Continue|The Turning Point]]

:: The Turning Point [cluster1 passage]
Over the past year small groups have tested this system.

The largest run happened on February 21 during a birthday gathering. Dozens of players entered the story at once.

The system held.

Two weeks later the circumstances of my life shifted in a way that created space to focus on building this work fully.

The Bruised Banana Residency is the container for the next phase.

[[Continue|The Invitation]]

:: The Invitation [cluster1 passage]
You've arrived while this next chapter is beginning.

Some people will help build the system.
Some will test it by playing.
Some will support the residency so the work can continue.

Before you step further into the campaign, there's a simple question.

How does this land for you?

[[This sounds exciting. I want to see what's possible here.|Aligned Response]]
[[I'm curious, though I'm still figuring out where I fit.|Curious Response]]
[[I'm skeptical. Systems like this rarely work the way people hope.|Skeptical Response]]

:: Aligned Response [cluster1 choice aligned emotional-alchemy]
[TOKEN] SET emotional_alchemy=aligned

Something in this already feels alive.

Good. You don't need the whole map in advance. You only need a direction worth stepping toward.

Let's make your role in the story visible.

[[Continue|Why Identity Matters]]

:: Curious Response [cluster1 choice neutral emotional-alchemy]
[TOKEN] SET emotional_alchemy=curious

Curiosity is enough.

You don't need certainty to begin. The campaign can meet you before you know exactly what part you want to play.

Let's make your role in the story visible.

[[Continue|Why Identity Matters]]

:: Skeptical Response [cluster1 choice divergent emotional-alchemy]
[TOKEN] SET emotional_alchemy=skeptical

Skepticism has its uses.

A system like this should earn belief through experience. The next steps are simple enough to test whether the structure holds.

Let's make your role in the story visible.

[[Continue|Why Identity Matters]]

:: Why Identity Matters [cluster2 passage]
Every story becomes more interesting when characters are distinct.

Some people naturally connect allies who would otherwise never meet. Some see structural patterns others miss. Some stabilize tension when situations become charged.

The game works best when it understands how players move through situations.

Nations and archetypes give the system that map. The clearer your starting point, the more interesting the quests it can generate for you.

[[Choose your Nation|Choose Nation]]

:: Choose Nation [cluster2 template choose-one]
The world of the campaign is shaped by different cultural environments.

Each nation represents a different approach to collaboration, strategy, and risk.

Read about each nation before choosing. You can always return to this list.

[[Read about Argyra|Nation_Argyra_Info]]
[[Read about Pyrakanth|Nation_Pyrakanth_Info]]
[[Read about Lamenth|Nation_Lamenth_Info]]
[[Read about Meridia|Nation_Meridia_Info]]
[[Read about Virelune|Nation_Virelune_Info]]

:: Nation_Argyra_Info [cluster2 info]
**Argyra — The Silver City**

Elegant coordination, precision, and social patterning. The silver mirror: clarity, structure, and precision. When you channel Argyran energy, problems become solvable because you can see the structure underneath the chaos.

[Learn more about Argyra](/wiki/nations)

[[Choose this nation|Nation_Argyra]]
[[Back to list|Choose Nation]]

:: Nation_Pyrakanth_Info [cluster2 info]
**Pyrakanth — The Burning Garden**

Momentum, courage, heat, and decisive action. The blazing vanguard: passion, transformation, and fire. Pyrakanth gardens with fire—growth requires both wild passion and devoted tending.

[Learn more about Pyrakanth](/wiki/nations)

[[Choose this nation|Nation_Pyrakanth]]
[[Back to list|Choose Nation]]

:: Nation_Lamenth_Info [cluster2 info]
**Lamenth — The Weeping Stone**

Depth, grief, memory, and emotional truth. The deep current: emotion, intuition, and flow. Lamenth holds what others rush past—memory, grief, and the wisdom that comes from depth.

[Learn more about Lamenth](/wiki/nations)

[[Choose this nation|Nation_Lamenth]]
[[Back to list|Choose Nation]]

:: Nation_Meridia_Info [cluster2 info]
**Meridia — The Golden Noon**

Coherence, stewardship, and grounded flourishing. The grounded center: stability, nurture, and endurance. Meridia stands at high noon, where light eliminates shadows—clear sight, fair exchange, and win-win thinking.

[Learn more about Meridia](/wiki/nations)

[[Choose this nation|Nation_Meridia]]
[[Back to list|Choose Nation]]

:: Nation_Virelune_Info [cluster2 info]
**Virelune — The Green Moon**

Mystery, emergence, intuition, and hidden pathways. The living network: growth, connection, and creativity. Virelune prefers to grow around obstacles rather than smash them. Respect.

[Learn more about Virelune](/wiki/nations)

[[Choose this nation|Nation_Virelune]]
[[Back to list|Choose Nation]]

